Visualization: Case 1- Objective Optimize maintenance schedules for multi-unit plants, particularly those using natural gas. 5


Positive Insight:
NG (Natural Gas) plants have a high average capacity of 157.78 MW. These plants produce significant energy indicating high capacity.




Negative Insight:
Multi-unit plants, such as NG plants, require more downtime for maintenance, leading to production delays.  NG plants correlate with higher maintenance percentages(61%), highlighting their longer downtime for maintenance.




Case 1 ROI:
Optimizing maintenance for NG multi-unit plants could lead to an annual savings of $45.3M by reducing downtime and enhancing plant longevity. The  relationship between plant size and maintenance costs, helping to estimate potential savings.
